1. - About "Ye Olde Pong"

"Ye Olde Pong" is a clone of the Pong game that was released on the
Atari 2600 platform during the early 80's. The purpose of this program
is primarily to familiarize the authors with working with outside
libraries, but the SDL library in particular. As was mentioned before,
this program is based on SDL and is very simple in nature.

2.1 - Hardware Requirements

"Ye Olde Pong" does not really put a strain on your hardware, so any
computer that is capable of running X ought to be able to handle it.

2.2 - Software Requirements

"Ye Olde Pong" depends on the following:

GNU g++ compiler
libsdl1.2-dev

3. - Installation/Compilation

In order to compile "Ye Olde Pong" you just have to be in the
program's root directory and run "make". There is no "configure"
executable for this program, so running the Makefile is all that is
necessary.

4. - License

"Ye Olde Pong" is licensed under the New BSD license. For more
information, read the COPYING file in the program's root directory.

